# Coding Rules

## General Principles

- Always keep it simple
- Prefer using Tailwind CSS over CSS
- Prefer server actions over API routes in Next.js
- Never comment out code
- Always ask for clarification when description is not clear
- Prefer using Functional approach over Class based approach
- Always look for obsolete code and remove it, but verify with the user first

## Code Formatting & Linting

### Biome Configuration

The project uses Biome for formatting and linting with these settings:

```json
{
  "formatter": {
    "enabled": true,
    "indentStyle": "space",
    "indentWidth": 2
  },
  "linter": {
    "enabled": true,
    "rules": {
      "recommended": true
    },
    "domains": {
      "next": "recommended",
      "react": "recommended"
    }
  }
}
```

## Performance Guidelines

- Optimize for performance
- Use proper React patterns
- Minimize unnecessary re-renders
- Use proper error handling
- Log errors appropriately

## Error Handling

- Implement proper error handling
- Use user-friendly error messages
- Log errors appropriately
- Handle authentication errors gracefully
